        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=73133&amp;TOPIC_ID=8464&amp;FORUM_ID=17&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=Rant+Forum&amp;Topic_Title=Wurmslayer+I+hate+this+weapon&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         The wurmy will still outdamage a lammy into the low 50's in terms of raw hp dmg. However, because of the delay it will not maintain aggro too good. I would say level 53 or thereabouts would be a good time to switch, unless of course you're the MA.</P><P>The primary hand damage bonus only starts kicking in the low 50's. It's not like you get a sudden increase in power.</P><P>Based on my 54 ranger's experience.</P><P>Bonekasta, 51 Necromancer<BR>TALLON ZEK<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
